physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Initial perineal inspection revealed induration of the perianal skin. Digital rectal examination showed anal stenosis without tenderness or bulging. Pelvic examination showed posterior vaginal wall tenderness and a small opening draining purulent exudate.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Three months later, examination revealed a perianal orifice compatible with the external opening of a fistula-in-ano. Two weeks later, hypogastric tenderness was noted. Three days after that, physical examination was unremarkable except for continued hypogastric tenderness.
